article.headline: High Point 67, Presbyterian 48
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. -- Corey Law scored 18 points and grabbed 15 rebounds to help High Point defeat Presbyterian 67-48 in the regular-season finale for both teams on Saturday night. The Panthers (15-14, 10-8 Big South Conference) outrebounded the Blue Hose 43-33, and held a 24-12 advantage in the paint. High Point shot 44.4 percent in the first half (12 of 27), while Presbyterian (5-26, 2-16) shot 29.6 percent (8 of 27) before halftime. The Panthers used a 10-2 run in the final 5:48 of the first half to lead 32-22 at halftime. Khalid Mutakabbir's 3-pointer pulled the Blue Hose pulled within 34-33 with 16:12 left, before High Point pulled away. The Panthers answered with an 11-2 run, capped by two free throws by Eugene Harris with 12:41 remaining. Nick Barbour had 17 points for High Point, which scored 17 points off 13 turnovers. Ryan Hargrave paced Presbyterian with 12 points.
